 <fr:p>This follows in essentially the same way as <fr:link
href="jms-00BH.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00BH">sections need not be embeddings</fr:link>. Let <fr:tex>\mathcal {K}</fr:tex> be <fr:tex>\mathbf {Cat}</fr:tex> and consider the circle <fr:tex>S^1</fr:tex> viewed as the free groupoid generated by a point and a loop. Then the base point <fr:tex>\mathbf {1} \xrightarrow { \mathsf { base } } S^1</fr:tex> is not fully faithful, as there are <fr:tex>\mathbb {Z}</fr:tex> many endomorphisms on <fr:tex>\mathsf { base }</fr:tex> that do not lie in the image of <fr:tex>\mathbf {1} \xrightarrow { \mathsf { base } } S^1</fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
